I"¹<p>This photographic long-term project documents the retreat of the human presence from remote rural areas in the Alps. It studies the human/ non-human relationship in a landscape shaped by human labour  for centuries.</p>

<figure><figcaption><span>Abandonded cave in the Ossola Valley in the Northern Piedmont, Italy. The artefacts abandoned in the landscape are reminders of a co-habitation between humans and non-humans. <br /><em>David Loher, 2021</em> </span></figcaption><img src="/assets/img/imagequilt-stone.png" /></figure>

<p>With a particular focus on the remains of non-agricultural activities, the project examines through image and text how these remote areas were shaped by various industries, and not only by agriculture.
